results.name: Semiprimes from partition of sequence of positive integers.
comment: Partition the sequence of positive integers into groups of numbers that sum up to semiprimes: {1, 2, 3}, {4}, {5..8}, {9}, {10}, {11..15}, {16, 17}, {18..20}, {21}, {22}, {23..35}, {36..38}, {39}, {40..42}, {43, 44}, etc. Corresponding semiprimes are: 6, 4, 26, 9, 10, 65, 33, 57, 21, 22, 377, 111, 39, 123, 87,  etc.
Is the sequence finite? See comment in A109411.
link: Zak Seidov, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
results.author: _Zak Seidov_, Sep 26 2007
